We develop the site on the branch gh-pages. 
The url for the site will be: <username>.github.io/nargar (project name).

To get it running I had to install ruby with brew (to /usr).

Had to run gem install --user-install ffi -- --enable-libffi-alloc as per https://github.com/ffi/ffi/issues/864
-------------

bundle exec jekyll serve

---------

Note that the default markdown parser used by Jekyll is 'kramdown'.

----------

I use sudo bundle exec jekyll serve for local development. 
